Tonyville first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/> 

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Tonyville had a population of 329. The population density was {{convert|6,580.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tonyville was 51 (15.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 4 (1.2%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 232 (70.5%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 40 (12.2%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 321 persons (97.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Tonyville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0678932 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 74 households, out of which 45 (60.8%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 47 (63.5%) were married-couple households, 3 (4.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 13 (17.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 11 (14.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 4 households (5.4%) were one person, and 1 (1.4%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.45.<ref name=DP1/> There were 67 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (90.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Tonyville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0678932 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 123 people (37.4%) under the age of 18, 25 people (7.6%) aged 18 to 24, 81 people (24.6%) aged 25 to 44, 61 people (18.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 39 people (11.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 28.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 115.0 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 77 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,540.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 74 (96.1%) were occupied. Of these, 21 (28.4%) were owner-occupied, and 53 (71.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

